#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Play Time}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can estimate your \\textbf{minimal} play time using the following formula:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\begin{center}\n"
"  Play Time $= \\boldsymbol{P × R × 5}$ [min]\n"
"\\end{center}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Where:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item[$\\textbf{P}$] -- number of players\n"
"  \\item[$\\textbf{R}$] -- number of rounds\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Therefore, if you're playing a 3-player scenario consisting of 12 rounds, you can easily calculate that $3 × 12 × 5 = 180$.\n"
"Your expected minimal play time should be around 3 hours.\n"
"To calculate the \\textbf{upper bound} of your play time (more realistic if there are inexperienced players), just double the result.\n"
"So in this case that would be 6 hours.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Magic Arrows}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Except for the Magic Arrow, every spell appears exactly twice in the spell deck.\n"
"After players prepare their starting M\\&M decks, it is recommended to remove as many Magic Arrows from the spell deck, so that at most two of them remain.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Trading Post}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although rules as written state that you can remove only one card from your hand while visiting a Trading Post, it is recommended to allow removing as many as you like.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

